remarks.format:
## Remarks

`HBColor` represents a HarfBuzz color value (`hb_color_t`). The underlying 32-bit integer stores channels in BGRA byte order: blue in the high byte, then green, then red, and alpha in the low byte (`0xBBGGRRAA`). This differs from <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, which uses ARGB order (`0xAARRGGBB`).

Use the named properties <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Red>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Green>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Blue>, and <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Alpha> to access individual channels without worrying about byte order.

`HBColor` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from individual RGBA components
var color = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 128, blue: 0, alpha: 255);
Console.WriteLine(color.Red);   // 255
Console.WriteLine(color.Green); // 128

// Convert from SKColor
SKColor skColor = SKColors.CornflowerBlue;
HBColor hbColor = skColor.ToHBColor();
```
